The paper focuses on question generation, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a multi-task learning approach, which involves language modeling, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The paper also uses attention-based pointer generator models, which are commonly used in neural networks, suggesting that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on SQuAD and MARCO datasets, which are commonly used in information retrieval tasks, indicating that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
